The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for text summarization, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses different types of model architectures and learning schemas, which are related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions transferable knowledge, which is related to information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses achieving state-of-the-art results, which is related to neural networks (NN) and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
